                                <date>1958</date>. С. <biblScope unit="page">??–??</biblScope>.</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><encodingDesc><tagsDecl>&amp;renditions;</tagsDecl></encodingDesc></teiHeader><text><body><entry xml:id="entry_ʒyx" xml:lang="os"><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>ʒyx</orth></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>ʒux</orth><form type="variant"><orth>c’ux</orth></form></form><sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>рот</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>mouth</q></tr></sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>пасть</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>maw</q></tr></sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>отверствие (ружья, сосуда)</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>bottleneck</q></tr></sense></sense><re><form type="lemma"><orth>ʒyxǵyn</orth></form><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>речистый</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>eloquent</q></tr></sense></re><re><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>fydʒyx</orth></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>fudcʼux</orth></form><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>сквернослов</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>ribald</q></tr></sense></re><re><form type="lemma"><orth>ʒyxæj</orth></form><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>устно</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>orally</q></tr></sense></re><exampleGrp><example><quote>...æmæ jyn galy aǧd jæ ʒyxy akodta</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>...и положил ему в рот бычью ляжку</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>...and he put an ox thigh into his mouth</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Munk."/><biblScope>34</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>dæ ʒyxy ʒyrd ænæ rædyd nyccævy zærdæjy kæron</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>слово твоих уст безошибочно поражает край сердца</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>the word of your mouth infallibly strikes at the edge of the heart</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>112</biblScope></bibl></example></exampleGrp><re><form type="lemma"><orth>kæræʒī ʒyxæj īsyn</orth></form><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>говорить наперебой („брать из уст друг у друга“)</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>to speak interrupting each other (“to take out of each other's mouths”):</q></tr></sense><exampleGrp><example><quote>rtæ razzag sylgojmaǵy qaræg kæræʒī ʒyxæj īsync</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>три передние женщины причитают, (подхватывая причитания) из уст друг у друга</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>the three women in the front wail, taking lamentations from each other's mouths</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Čerm."/><biblScope>117</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>dæ ʒyxyl xæc!</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>держи язык за зубами!</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>hold your tongue!</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Брит."/><biblScope>149</biblScope></bibl></example></exampleGrp></re><re><form type="lemma"><orth>toppy ʒyx</orth></form><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>отверстие ружейного дула</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>edge of the gun</q></tr></sense></re><exampleGrp><example><quote>...æmæ jyn galy aǧd jæ ʒyxy akodta</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>...и положил ему в рот бычью ляжку</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>...and he put an ox thigh into his mouth</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Munk."/><biblScope>34</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>dæ ʒyxy ʒyrd ænæ rædyd nyccævy zærdæjy kæron</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>слово твоих уст безошибочно поражает край сердца</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>the word of your mouth infallibly strikes at the edge of the heart</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>112</biblScope></bibl></example></exampleGrp><etym xml:lang="ru">Ос. %iʒyx%i | %icʼux%i имеет близкие параллели в кавказских языках, а также в русских говорах: <mentioned xml:lang="x-vaynakh"><lang/> <w>z’ok, ʒok</w> <gloss><q>клюв</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="krc-x-balkar"><lang/> <w>ǯux</w> <gloss><q>рот</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="krc-x-balkar"><w/> <gloss><q>морда</q></gloss></mentioned>,  (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>280</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="ab"><lang/> <w>a-č’ə</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="uby"><lang/> <w>čε</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ady-x-abadz"><lang/> <w>že</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kbd"><lang/> <w>žeh</w></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Ногма"/><biblScope>158</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="kbd"><lang/> <w>, ž’e</w> <gloss><q>рот</q></gloss></mentioned>; <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/> <w>чуха</w> <gloss><q>рыло</q></gloss></mentioned>%b(сиб.)%b, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/> <w>чуха</w> <gloss><q>нижняя челюсть</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ru"><w/> <gloss><q>подбородок</q></gloss></mentioned>, %b(перм., вят.)%b. Возможна древняя метатеза из *%ikuč%i; см. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_gūcʼa"/> ‘глотка’.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>78, 105, 118, 314</biblScope></bibl>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">Ossetic %iʒyx%i | %icʼux%i has close correspondences in Caucasian languages, as well as in Russian dialects: <mentioned xml:lang="x-vaynakh"><lang/> <w>z’ok, ʒok</w> <gloss><q>beak</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="krc-x-balkar"><lang/> <w>ǯux</w> <gloss><q>mouth</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="krc-x-balkar"><w/> <gloss><q>maw</q></gloss></mentioned>,  (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>280</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="ab"><lang/> <w>a-č’ə</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="uby"><lang/> <w>čε</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ady-x-abadz"><lang/> <w>že</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kbd"><lang/> <w>žeh</w></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Ногма"/><biblScope>158</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="kbd"><lang/> <w>ž’e</w> <gloss><q>mouth</q></gloss></mentioned>; <mentioned xml:lang="ru-x-sib"><lang/> <w>чуха</w> <gloss><q>snout</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru" dialect="ru-x-perm ru-x-vyat"><lang/> <w>чуха</w> <gloss><q>lower jaw</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ru" dialect="ru-x-perm ru-x-vyat"><w/> <gloss><q>chin</q></gloss></mentioned>, . An ancient metathesis from *%ikuč%i is possible; see <ref type="xr" target="#entry_gūcʼa"/> ‘throat’.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>78, 105, 118, 314</biblScope></bibl>.</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>